# Force LF for anything that runs as a shell script inside a Linux container,
# regardless of the checkout OS's core.autocrlf setting. Without this, a
# Windows checkout (core.autocrlf=true) converts backend/mvnw to CRLF, which
# breaks its "#!/bin/sh" shebang inside the Alpine Docker build stage
# ("/bin/sh: ./mvnw: not found") — a real build-breaking bug, not a style nit.
* text=auto eol=lf
*.bat text eol=crlf
*.cmd text eol=crlf
